answers.body_markdown:
As denoted in the comments already, there are two issues in your code:

At first, `std::priority_queue` requires strict weak ordering (just as any other sorted container like `std::set` or `std::map`, see notes on [`Compare` template parameter](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/container/priority_queue)), in other words, elements must not compare equal to themselves. So you need to replace

    return *a.first &gt;= *b.first;
    //              ^^

with

    return *a.first &gt; *b.first;
    //              ^

At second, you do not consider empty vectors – unless explicitly excluded by the task, you need to do so:

    for(auto&amp; arr: arrays)
    {
        if(!arr.empty()) { /*...*/ }
    }

Otherwise, `*it.first` will dereference the end iterator and `it.first + 1` increments it.

Optimisation opportunity: avoid reallocations inside the target vector:

    size_t totalSize = 0;
    for(auto&amp; arr: arrays)
    {
        if(!arr.empty())
        {
            totalSize += arr.size();
            /*...*/
        }
    }
    result.reserve(totalSize);

